+config DOOR_LOCK_TIME_CONCEPT_PERSIST
+	bool "Persist the wall clock and restore it after reboot"
+	default y
+	depends on DOOR_LOCK_TIME_CONCEPT && SETTINGS
+	help
+	  The reader wall clock lives in RAM and the commissioner sets it
+	  exactly once at commissioning, so any reboot leaves the reader
+	  without valid time. If enabled, the wall clock is written to the
+	  settings storage once per hour (and shortly after it first becomes
+	  valid or is corrected), and the system clock is seeded from the
+	  stored value at boot. After a reboot time then resumes at worst
+	  one hour plus the power-off duration behind real time instead of
+	  being absent. The restored clock understates real time by that
+	  amount, which weakens validUntil/expiry and schedule enforcement
+	  correspondingly but never moves the clock backward or forward
+	  beyond what was actually observed.
